$$\begin{aligned}
\frac{a^{2}}{b+c}+\frac{b^{2}}{c+a}= & \frac{a^{2}(c+a)+b^{2}(b+c)}{(b+c)(c+a)}=\frac{a^{3}+b^{3}+c\left(a^{2}+b^{2}\right)}{(b+c)(c+a)} \geqslant \\
& \frac{a^{2} b+a b^{2}+c(2 a b)}{(b+c)(c+a)}=\frac{a b(c+a)+a b(b+c)}{(b+c)(c+a)}= \\
& \frac{a b}{b+c}+\frac{a b}{c+a}
\end{aligned}$$

Similarly,
$$\begin{array}{l}
\frac{b^{2}}{c+a}+\frac{c^{2}}{a+b} \geqslant \frac{b c}{c+a}+\frac{b c}{a+b} \\
\frac{a^{2}}{b+c}+\frac{c^{2}}{a+b} \geqslant \frac{a c}{b+c}+\frac{a c}{a+b}
\end{array}$$

Adding the three inequalities and simplifying, we get
$$\begin{aligned}
\frac{a^{2}}{b+c}+\frac{b^{2}}{c+a}+\frac{c^{2}}{a+b} \geqslant \frac{a(b+c)}{b+c}+\frac{b(c+a)}{c+a}+\frac{c(a+b)}{a+b}= \\
\frac{a+b+c}{2}
\end{aligned}$$

